  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca 90%\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "90% of India's urea fertilizers have been distributed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Department of Agricultural Services says that 90 percent of the urea fertilizers given by the Indian government will be distributed.",
        "According to the Ministry of Agriculture, 23,254.89 metric tons of urea fertilizer had been distributed among 490,515 farmers and the total amount of paddy cultivated by them was 304,734.08 hectares.",
        "The ministry stated that out of the 65,000 metric tons that were to be provided by the Indian government, 41,000 metric tons had been received as the first stock and the remaining 24,000 metric tons of urea would be received in the near future.",
        "Minister Mahinda Amaraweera said that 15,000 metric tons of this urea fertilizer has been allocated for tea cultivation, 40,000 metric tons for paddy cultivation and 10,000 metric tons for maize cultivation."
      ],
